                   Part 3 - Design
1:  Designing a simple REST API for a library system

    crud- create, getAll, getById, delete, update
    @PostMapping create- create new user / book / order.
    @GetMapping getAll- get all users / books / orders
    @GetMapping("/{id}") getById- get user/ book / order by id
    @PutMapping("/{id}") update- update user/ book / order by id
    @DeleteMapping("/{id}") delete- delete user/ book / order by id

    user /
    •	Id*
    •	Name*
    •	Address*
    •	Phone*
    •	Age
    •	OrdersId []*

    Order/
    •	Id*
    •	UserId (foreign key)*
    •	BookId (foreign key)*
    •	BorrowDate*
    •	LibrrayReturningDate*
    •	ReturningDate

    Book /
    •	Id*
    •	Name*
    •	Author
    •	PlaceInLibrrary*

    (* - is required field)

2:  Design departments for an order + payment system

    Customers/
    Customer information (CRUD) – customer connect between order to payment.
    Products/
    Information of the products.
    Orders/
    Management the orders, the products, state of the order.
    Payments/
    Manage order payments by array of orderId and details about the payment
    The field orderId in Payment is required.
